{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Agent Identity SDK: API Key Usage Example\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook demonstrates how to interactively use the `agent-identity-dev-sdk` to automatically manage workload access tokens and seamlessly inject API keys into decorated functions.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Prerequisites\n",
    "\n",
    "Before running the remaining cells, ensure you have set your **Huawei Cloud AK/SK** credentials and the desired region. You can set them here or rely on your environment.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Note:** You can also customize the endpoint for the Agent Identity service in a specific region using an environment variable like `HUAWEICLOUD_SDK_REGION_AGENTIDENTITY_{REGION_ID}={endpoint}`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os\n",
    "\n",
    "# Manually set your credentials here for testing if not already in your environment.\n",
    "# Ensure you DO NOT commit these secrets to version control.\n",
    "\n",
    "# os.environ[\"HUAWEICLOUD_SDK_AK\"] = \"your-access-key-id\"\n",
    "# os.environ[\"HUAWEICLOUD_SDK_SK\"] = \"your-secret-access-key\"\n",
    "# os.environ[\"HUAWEICLOUD_SDK_REGION\"] = \"cn-southwest-301\"\n",
    "# os.environ[\"HUAWEICLOUD_SDK_PROJECT_ID\"] = \"your-project-id\"\n",
    "# os.environ[\"HUAWEICLOUD_SDK_DOMAIN_ID\"] = \"your-domain-id\"\n",
    "\n",
    "# (Optional) Customize the endpoint for a specific region\n",
    "# os.environ[\"HUAWEICLOUD_SDK_REGION_AGENTIDENTITY_CN_SOUTHWEST_301\"] = \"https://agent-identity-open.cn-southwest-301.beta.myhuaweicloud.com\"\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Environment variables ready.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import uuid\n",
    "from typing import Optional\n",
    "from agentarts.sdk import AgentArtsRuntimeContext, require_api_key, IdentityClient\n",
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Step 1: Set the Context\n",
    "\n",
    "The SDK relies on contextual information (like `user_id`) being set before operations occur.\n",
    "Here, we generate unique identifiers for this session and seed our `AgentIdentityContext`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# 0. Generate random identifiers for testing\n",
    "random_suffix = uuid.uuid4().hex[:8]\n",
    "user_id = f\"user-{random_suffix}\"\n",
    "workload_name = f\"workload-for-{user_id}\"\n",
    "\n",
    "# 1. Set the user ID for context\n",
    "AgentArtsRuntimeContext.set_user_id(user_id)\n",
    "print(f\"Context set for User ID: {user_id}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Step 2: Initialize the Identity Client\n",
    "\n",
    "We construct the `IdentityClient` that will be used to interact with Huawei Cloud services."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# 2. Initialize IdentityClient using the region from the environment\n",
    "region = os.getenv(\"HUAWEICLOUD_SDK_REGION\", \"cn-southwest-301\")\n",
    "client = IdentityClient(region=region, ignore_ssl_verification=True)\n",
    "print(f\"IdentityClient initialized for region: {region}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Step 3: Create an API Key Credential Provider\n",
    "\n",
    "Before we can request an API key, we must first register the credential provider with the identity service.\n",
    "We will dynamically create a provider name for this session."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# 3. Create an API Key Credential Provider\n",
    "api_key_provider_name = f\"my-llm-provider-{random_suffix}\"\n",
    "print(f\"Creating API Key Credential Provider: {api_key_provider_name}...\")\n",
    "try:\n",
    "    provider = client.create_api_key_credential_provider(\n",
    "        name=api_key_provider_name, api_key=\"sk-dummy-api-key-12345\"\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    print(f\"Successfully created provider: {provider.name}\")\n",
    "except Exception as e:\n",
    "    print(f\"Provider might already exist or creation failed: {e}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Step 4: Define the Target Function\n",
    "\n",
    "Now we define our target function (`call_llm`).\n",
    "We decorate this function with `@require_api_key(provider_name=api_key_provider_name)` so the SDK handles API key injection automatically."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Note: We use the dynamically generated provider name from the previous step\n",
    "@require_api_key(provider_name=api_key_provider_name, ignore_ssl_verification=True)\n",
    "def call_llm(api_key: Optional[str] = None) -> None:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Calls an LLM service with an API key.\n",
    "\n",
    "    Args:\n",
    "        api_key: The API key injected automatically by the SDK.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    print(f\"Using API Key: {api_key}\")\n",
    "    # Your actual LLM call logic would go here...\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Decorated function defined.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Step 5: Create a Workload Identity\n",
    "\n",
    "Next, we register our uniquely named workload identity with the Identity service."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# 3. Create a workload identity\n",
    "from huaweicloudsdkagentidentity.v1 import (\n",
    "    AuthorizerType,\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Creating workload identity: {workload_name}...\")\n",
    "# 'authorizer_type' is now a mandatory parameter in the underlying SDK.\n",
    "# The SDK wrapper defaults it to AuthorizerType.NONE if not specified.\n",
    "workload = client.create_workload_identity(\n",
    "    name=workload_name, authorizer_type=AuthorizerType.NONE\n",
    ")\n",
    "print(f\"Created Workload: {workload.name}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Step 6: Fetch Workload Access Token\n",
    "\n",
    "Using our registered workload and user ID, we request an access token. The SDK needs this token to authorize fetching specific API keys."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# 4. Get workload access token\n",
    "print(f\"Getting workload access token for {workload.name} and user {user_id}...\")\n",
    "token = client.create_workload_access_token(\n",
    "    workload_name=workload.name, user_id=user_id\n",
    ")\n",
    "print(\"Workload access token successfully retrieved.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Step 7: Inject the Token and Call the Function\n",
    "\n",
    "Finally, we place the retrieved token into our `AgentIdentityContext`.\n",
    "When we call `call_llm()`, the `@require_api_key` decorator will use this token automatically to fetch the dynamically created API key and pass it into the function."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# 5. Set the retrieved token in the context\n",
    "AgentArtsRuntimeContext.set_workload_access_token(token)\n",
    "\n",
    "# 6. Call the decorated function\n",
    "print(\"Calling the decorated function...\")\n",
    "call_llm()\n",
    "print(\"Execution complete!\")"
   ]
  }
 ],
